scene.message:
Doctor: Well, I'll be off...{nl}
Make sure you get{nl}
some fresh air sometimes.{nl}
Rehab is important.{waitkey}{ret}

Nurse: That's right, Maki.{nl}
Let's go for a little{nl}
walk tomorrow.{waitkey}{ret}

{color:3}Sonohara Maki{nl}
A classmate hospitalized{nl}
for nearly a year.{nl}
Has been ill since childhood.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Doctor: Hmm?{nl}
Looks like the best{nl}
medicine just arrived.{nl}
We'll take our leave.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: {ctl0f:1}...{nl}
You all came...{nl}
thank you.{waitkey}{nl}
Inaba, you arranged this,{nl}
didn't you?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: The last time Inaba{nl}
visited, I said I wanted{nl}
to see everyone...{wait_fr:94}{nl}
Wasn't that why?{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: ...It sure was.{nl}
{wait_fr:88}Oh, and Himeno's{nl}
coming to return a book —{nl}
"The Gate of Paradise."{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: I see... she didn't{nl}
have to bother.{nl}
I've read it so many{nl}
times I know it by heart.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Got it, I'll{nl}
let her know.{wait_fr:88}{nl}
But more importantly —{nl}
how are you doing?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Better than before,{nl}
actually. Maybe because{nl}
I've been having nice{nl}
dreams lately...{waitkey}{clearbox}I can't remember them{nl}
well, but there's this very{nl}
gentle man in them...{nl}
Like a father figure...{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: It's not that...{nl}
I just don't like{nl}
doctors.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Well, forget about{nl}
that for now!{nl}
So — what about{nl}
your mom?{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: She's not my mom!{nl}
She cares more about{nl}
her job than me!{wait_fr:94}{nl}
I don't matter to her...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: This place...{nl}
smells like Sonohara...{nl}
{wait_fr:88}Sonohara... I'm gonna{nl}
find you, I swear.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: I'm worried about{nl}
Sonohara, but... let's{nl}
get out to the streets.{nl}
Something feels wrong.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: {ctl0f:1}{nl}
What about Sonohara's{nl}
mother? We'd better hurry{nl}
or it'll be too late.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: ...{nl}
Is this Maki's room?{nl}
It feels... so lonely.{waitkey}{ret}
